text: I sincerely hope that the Ministry of Education is aware of the risks by sending all kids back to school. All as in even the graduating cohorts. Should anything amiss happens, many parents like myself will be absolutely furious. PREVENTION IS BETTER THAN GRADUATION. Being at home for too long isnt good for their mental well being but being at school at this point of time may affect their mentality greatly. Can the kids concentrate? Can the teachers perform? We must remember that our mental state is most important. Hence, we must not mix fear with education. Yes, they have careful measures to protect the kids but they cannot GUARANTEE that the kids will be safe from the virus. During HBL, the kids were safe at 🏡 home. WHY CANT THE CHILDREN (STUDENTS OF ALL AGES) BE PUT IN PHASE 3?

answers.text: @assasinized.yeti I respect yr preference. I too as a parent will prefer school over hbl. My eldest son is going to NUS soon and my youngest is taking PSLE this yr. But at this point of time, I will choose health than face to face school. We can always u-turn on school or education but we cant u-turn on a life. We can postpone education but we cant postpone on a life. We are humans and as a human, I choose to think wisely and value what is most precious and hard to find and hard to get back. The Govt is not giving parents options but make it compulsory. It is therefore a great worry for me. It takes a long time to produce my children and hence, I value my children more than anything. Study with happiness but not with fear. A child can absorb with happiness but not with fear.

I feel like the kids has to undergo this everyday esp for graduation cohorts and I fear for my child's mentality. When kids are stressed, parents will too. There are 40 students in my son's classroom. You can't fully expect the teacher to be responsible for all. The teacher has many things to do and remember.
